Great teacher meeting today!
We have moved enrollment to August 10 and 11th. Megan will be mailing out enrollment documents so it will be possible to enroll without physically being on campus. We will have another teacher meeting on July 24. We will have some Remote Learning information ready to send out after that meeting.

The following message is from the Kiowa County Schools Yearbook staff.

Due to COVID-19, we are having to make several changes in our yearbook. The yearbook staff would like your help. We would like you to email us pictures that represent your daily life during this unprecedented time. This could include at-home learning, outdoor activities, Zoom classes, family fun, etc. Please add a description for each of your pictures. Pictures off of phones need to be emailed at actual size. Please send your emails to yearbook@usd422.org.

Thank you,

Katie Spainhour, Yearbook Editor

post_text:
Congratulations Grayson!!
Grayson won our local "Who Was?" History Bee. He then took a proctored national test which entered him into a national Who Was? knowledge competition. We just got word yesterday that Grayson's score was one of the top 10 out of over 25,000 students who participated. He will get to travel to New York City in the fall to compete against the other 9 for a chance at a scholarship!! HGS will be well represented by Grayson Ballard!!!

post_text:
Governor Kelly's executive order to stay at home has probably raised some questions about our plan for next week. I want to reiterate our plan.

School Bag pickup-Please make an appointment or call in advance of showing up. Please pull up to the North sidewalk if your last name begins with A-M or the South sidewalk if your last name begins with N-Z. Pop your trunk and our staff will put your bags in your vehicle.
There will be a library book return box at both pickup points.

Meals-Bus routes: no change. Grab-N-Go locations just pull up, pop your trunk, and our staff will put your meals in your trunk.

Continuous Learning Plan - This executive order will not change our current learning plan.
Stay Safe!!

Getting close to "roll out time!"
I hope you are all excited! We are!!
Recommended Time Guidelines:
K-1 30-45 minutes per day
2-4 60 minutes per day
5-6 90 minutes per day
7-8 3 hours per day
The teachers will send out instructions with their bags on Monday. Those time frames are for the required work, and then there will be enrichment activities if the students want more material.
Stay well Haviland!!!

Wednesday is going be a great day!! Your HGS staff is working hard for you! Our Continuous Learning Plan is coming together.
Beginning on Monday we will start providing Grab-N-Go meals two days a week. Be sure to call in to the office if you are interested in this program.
Also on Monday, we will have a process in place to pick up your students personal effects and materials for learning. Instructions for this process will come out Thursday.
We continue to discourage activities at the HGS facilities to be able to keep Haviland friends and families safe. Thank you all for your flexibility and positive attitudes. Haviland is a great place to raise kids!!!

post_text: USD 474 will be offering breakfast and lunch sack meals to any student ages 1-18 in the Haviland District beginning Monday, March 30th. We will provide 2 in town grab-and-go locations (HGS and the city park) 11:30-12:00 and will deliver the meals to students in the country along the bus routes at about 12:00. We will provide 2 breakfasts and 2 lunches on Monday and on Wednesday. These meals will be at no cost to you. If you are interested in getting these meals, please contact the grade school office by Thursday, March 26th to be put on the list. 620-862-5277.

post_text:
Today, March 17, 2020 Governor Laura Kelly announced all school facilities will close for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. We are working with the Kansas State Department of Education to develop alternative learning opportunities for all students and will share more information soon.
We live in unsettling times. As we walk this path together, please know that we will be working diligently with you to continue to provide the students of our community with a quality education.
Stay safe and have a good evening.

post_text:
We are working to create a Home Ec. room for the K-8 students. Here are some of the items we are needing. If you find that you have extra and would like to donate them, we would be very grateful!!

1 electric stove, 2 microwave ovens, measuring spoons/cups, plates, silverware, spatulas, mixing bowls, cookie/cake pans, pots and pans, knives, spices, toasters, and 3-5 sewing machines.

I am sure there are many items that I am forgetting. Thanks!! Have a great summer!
